    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so you're saying the benefits of high-skilled immigration are a \"demonstrable principle\" but the negative effects of low-skilled immigration are just something that happens if it's \"poorly managed\"? it feels like you're framing the benefits as a factual certainty and the downsides as just a mistake in policy rather than a real economic drawback that some people actually argue is a systemic issue.",
